&lt;p&gt;Characters are defined by &lt;em&gt;ability scores&lt;/em&gt;. There are six ability scores in the game:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strength&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî represents a character‚Äôs physical might,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dexterity&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî represents agility and the ability to avoid danger,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Constitution&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî indicates a character‚Äôs overall health and well-being,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intelligence&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî represents raw knowledge and problem-solving ability,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wisdom&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî measures a character‚Äôs insight and the ability to evaluate a situation,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Charisma&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî indicates charm, persuasiveness, and the force of personality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go to &lt;a href=&quot;../../../185---TTRPG/050---Pathfinder/500---Rules/011---Ability-modifiers&quot; class=&quot;internal alias&quot; data-slug=&quot;185---TTRPG/050---Pathfinder/500---Rules/011---Ability-modifiers&quot;&gt;Table: Ability modifiers&lt;/a&gt; to see how to calculate modifiers out of scores.&lt;/p&gt;

